This paper discusses the debate between model-based and model-free learning in the context of robotics, specifically in the field of human-robot interaction (HRI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics and Automation). The paper also discusses the use of a "theory of mind" to model the human in HRI, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of these methods, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper is focused on the interaction between humans and robots, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
